o%20downgrade%20his%20police%20protection%2C%20telling%20a%20London%20court%20the%20prince%20had%20recently%20faced%20threats%20from%20paparazzi%20and%20even%20Al-Qaeda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Harry's%20split%20with%20the%20royal%20family%20in%202020%20and%20move%20to%20America%20with%20his%20wife%20Meghan%2C%20the%20government%20decided%20his%20security%20during%20visits%20to%20Britain%20would%20be%20decided%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKing%20Charles%20III's%20youngest%20son%20made%20a%20rare%20visit%20to%20London%20for%20the%20latest%20stage%20of%20the%20long-running%20legal%20saga%2C%20watching%20his%20appeal%20unfold%20from%20inside%20the%20Royal%20Courts%20of%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDressed%20in%20a%20dark%20suit%20with%20a%20blue%20patterned%20tie%2C%20he%20looked%20on%20in%20the%20courtroom%2C%20occasionally%20whispering%20to%20his%20solicitor%20and%20wrote%20in%20a%20notebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Harry%2C%2040%2C%20stopped%20being%20considered%20a%20working%20royal%20in%202020%2C%20the%20government%20decided%20he%20would%20not%20receive%20the%20%26quot%3Bsame%20degree%26quot%3B%20of%20publicly%20funded%20protection%20when%20in%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prince%20took%20legal%20action%20against%20the%20interior%20ministry%20in%202021%2C%20and%20after%20his%20initial%20case%20was%20rejected%20last%20year%2C%20he%20brought%20a%20challenge%20before%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyer%20Shaheed%20Fatima%20told%20the%20court%20the%20prince%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bsingled%20out%20for%20different%2C%20unjustified%20and%20inferior%20treatment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20submission%2C%20his%20lawyers%20highlighted%20threats%20made%20against%20the%20prince.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAl-Qaeda%20recently%20called%20for%20(Harry)%20to%20be%20murdered%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20and%20Meghan%20were%20%26quot%3Binvolved%20in%20a%20dangerous%20car%20pursuit%20with%20papara